  <name>Throne</name>
  <summary>Qt based cross-platform GUI proxy configuration manager</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Throne is a Qt based desktop GUI proxy utility, powered by the sing-box
      core. It is the successor of Nekoray and continues development with
      additional features, protocol support and stability improvements.
    </p>
    <p>Supported protocols include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>SOCKS and HTTP(S)</li>
      <li>Shadowsocks, Trojan, VMess, VLESS</li>
      <li>TUIC, Hysteria, Hysteria2, AnyTLS</li>
      <li>NaiveProxy, Juicity, TrustTunnel, ShadowTLS</li>
      <li>WireGuard and SSH</li>
      <li>Custom outbounds, custom configs and chained outbounds</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Subscriptions are supported in a variety of formats including share
      links, sing-box JSON, v2rayN, and limited Shadowsocks and Clash formats.
    </p>
  </description>
